JOHANNESBURG, August 31 The following are major news items in leading South
African Newspapers Monday: The Citizen: -- South African police had traced
and cleared a suspect fingered by a victim of the Planet Hollywood blast as
the possible bomber, police said Sunday. The Star: -- Small-and-medium
business, along with the man in the street, were likely to suffer most
acutely in the short term following last week's Johannesburg Stock Exchange
crash which saw the market shed an unprecedented 17 percent of its value,
economists said Sunday. Business Day: -- Some big banks have been hit hard
by the panic sell-off in the bond market sparked by Russia's inability to
pay its foreign debts, and are bracing themselves for more turmoil this
week.
